Package com.ibm.xmi.framework

Interface Summary
AssociationEnd This interface represents an association end in the framework object model.
Attribute This interface represents an attribute in the framework object model.
AttributeValue This interface represents a value of an attribute in the framework object model.
Classifier This interface represents a classifier in the framework object model, which is either a Datatype or an XMIClass.
Contained This interface represents a link end of an object in the framework object model, whose corresponding association end is across from an association end whose aggregation property is composition.
Container This interface represents a link end of an object in the framework object model, whose corresponding association end has an aggregation property set to composition.
Data This interface is the root interface for the interface hierarchy representing XMI data.
Datatype This interface represents a datatype in the framework object model.
DataValue This interface represents a value of an attribute whose type is a datatype in the framework object model.
DeclarationWriterAdapter You can implement this interface to allow the framework to write DTDs and schemas for your data that corresponds to framework classes and packages if your data does not implement framework interfaces or inherit from framework classes.
Enum This interface represents an enumeration data type in the framework object model, which is based on the Enumeration data type in UML.
EnumValue This interface represents a value of an attribute whose type is an enumeration in the framework object model.
Extension This interface represents an XMI extension.
Factory The purpose of this interface is to provide an API for the framework so it can create implementations of the Data hierarchy interfaces when loading XMI files.
Feature This interface represents a feature in the framework object model.
LinkEnd This interface represents a link end of an object in the framework object model.
ObjectValue This interface represents a value of an attribute whose type is a class in the framework object model.
ObjectWriterAdapter You can implement this interface to allow the framework to write objects to XMI files if those objects do not implement framework interfaces or inherit from implementation classes in the framework object model.
Package This interface represents a package in the framework object model.
ReaderAdapter You can implement this interface to allow the framework to load XMI files and make instances of your classes or your own data without those classes implementing framework interfaces or inheriting from framework classes.
Reference This interface represents a link end of an object in the framework object model, whose corresponding association end is not a composite or container.
Value This interface represents a value in the framework object model.
WriterAdapter This interface defines methods used by both the ObjectWriterAdapter interface and the DeclarationWriterAdapter interface.
XMIClass This interface represents a class; in most object-oriented systems, you can make instances of classes.
XMIObject This interface represents an XMI object, an instance of a class.
XMLElement

AdapterFactoryRegister The framework uses this class to obtain an instance of a factory that creates writer adapters and reader adapters.

DeclarationFactory This class converts XMI objects from UML 1.1 XMI 1.0 files to framework declarations.
DeclarationWriterAdapterImpl This class implements the DeclarationWriterAdapter interface, using the framework object model classes to get the data required by the framework.
DefaultDeclarationWriterAdapter This abstract class implements the DeclarationWriterAdapter interface, providing default implementations for the methods that are only needed if you want to use more advanced capabilities of XMI; the methods you need to implement are abstract.
DefaultObjectWriterAdapter This class is an abstract class that you can use to help you implement your own object writer adapter.
DefaultReaderAdapter You can use this abstract class to implement the ReaderAdapter interface.
EnumImpl This class implements the Enum interface.
EnumValueImpl This class implements the EnumValue interface.
ExtensionImpl This class implements the Extension interface.
FactoryAdapter The framework uses this class by default when loading XMI files to create XMI objects and values using the implementation classes for the data hierarchy.
FactoryRegister The framework uses this class to obtain an instance of a class that implements the Factory interface.
FeatureImpl This class implements the Feature interface.
LinkEndImpl This class implements the LinkEnd interface.
MIME2Java MIME2Java is a convenience class which handles conversions between MIME charset names and Java encoding names.
Model This class represents a framework model, which is a collection of packages, classes, and features in the framework object model.
Namespace This class represents an XML namespace.
ObjectInfo This class holds information about an object that the framework acquires when it parses an XMI file.
ObjectValueImpl This class implements the ObjectValue interface.
ObjectWriterAdapterImpl This class implements the ObjectWriterAdapter interface, using the framework object model classes to get the data required by the framework.
PackageImpl This class implements the Package interface.
ReaderAdapterImpl This default implementation is used by the framework to create constructs from the Data hierarchy, unless you write your own adapters and register your adapter factory with the framework.
ReferenceImpl This class implements the Reference interface.
TagValue2Handler This object interprets SAX events for the contents of extensions in an XMI file that are IBM XMI Toolkit extensions that contain sets of tag values.
TagValueHandler This object interprets SAX events for the contents of extensions in an XMI file that are IBM XMI Framework extensions that contain sets of tag values.
UML2DTD This class lets you create an XMI DTD from a UML 1.1 XMI 1.0 file containing a UML model.
UML2Java This class generates Java classes, and optionally, interfaces and packages, from a UML 1.1 model in an XMI 1.0 file.
UML2Schema This program lets you convert a UML 1.1 XMI 1.0 file to an XMI schema.
ValueImpl This class implements the Value interface.
ValueInfo This class holds information about a value that the framework gets when it parses an XMI file.
Workspace A workspace is a collection of Models and XMIFiles instances.
WriterAdapterImpl This default implementation is used by the framework when writing XMI files and XMI DTDs and schemas; it queries the Data hierarchy classes for the information requested by the framework.
XMIClassImpl This class implements the XMIClass interface.
XMIContainer This class holds XMI objects.
XMIDTD This class represents an XMI DTD.
XMIFile This class represents an XMI file.
XMIFile.Import An import is part of the header of an XMI file that identifies other files that are needed to work with the objects in an XMI file.
XMIFile.Metametamodel A metametamodel is part of the header of an XMI file that represents the metametamodel for the objects in the file.
XMIFile.Metamodel A metamodel is part of the header of an XMI file that represents the metamodel for the objects in the file.
XMIFile.Model A model is part of the header of an XMI file that represents the model for the objects in the file.
XMIFiles An XMIFiles object represents a collection of XMI files that have cross-file references.
XMIHandler This class implements the SAX handler class and passes the methods to the appropriate loader, which also implements the SAX handler base class.
XMILoad  
XMIMultiplicity This class contains the code to check whether a given string is a legal XML multiplicity, and code to convert multiplicities to XML schema multiplicities and XML DTD multiplicities.
XMIName This class contains the code to check whether a given name is a legal XMI name and to convert an arbitrary name to an XMI name by removing illegal XMI characters from the name.
XMIObjectImpl This class implements the XMIObject interface,
XMISchema This class represents an XMI schema.

Exception Summary
BadDefinerException This exception is thrown when setting a definer of the wrong type for an element.
BadNameException This exception is thrown if a name is not a legal XMI name; since the XMI names are used as the tag names of XML elements, XMI names must be legal XML tag names.
BadTypeException This exception is thrown if the type of a value or the value type of a feature could not be set to the given type.
ContainmentException This exception is thrown when you attempt to write an object that is contained more than once among the objects given to the XMIFile write method.
LibraryException XML4J parser exception which signals that the XML parser has detected an internal error of some sort.
NoExtensionException This exception is thrown when you attempt to delete an extension from an object but the object does not have the extension.
NoFeatureException This exception is thrown when you attempt to delete a feature from a XMIClass but the XMIClass does not have the feature.
NoIdException This exception is thrown when an id is required but has not been set; for example, when writing XMI data to an XMI file.
NoNameException This exception is thrown when a name is required but it hasn't been set; for example, when writing an XMI element to an XMI file.
NoValueException This exception is thrown when you attempt to delete a value from an object but the object does not have the value.
ProxyNotResolvableException This exception is thrown during XMIFiles.loadAll when a proxy cannot be resolved to avoid an infinite loop.
XMIException This is the root class for all exceptions thrown by the XMI application framework.
